# Map the @n3ary scope to GitHub Packages so consumers can
# `npm install @n3ary/neary-gtfs-spec` and friends.
#
# Authentication: in CI, the GITHUB_TOKEN secret is automatically
# picked up by `actions/setup-node` for installs. For local
# development, add a personal access token with `read:packages`
# scope to `~/.npmrc`:
#
#   //npm.pkg.github.com/:_authToken=ghp_xxxxxxxx
#
# Tokenless (public-only) install:
#   npm install @n3ary/neary-gtfs-spec  → fails with 401 in CI for private packages
#
# With the org's GitHub Actions runs set to use the
# `packages: read` permission (default), `npm install` in CI
# works automatically.
@n3ary:registry=https://npm.pkg.github.com
